### clearPrimaryClip

Added in[API level 28](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/manifest/uses-sdk-element#ApiLevels)  

```
public void clearPrimaryClip ()
```

Clears any current primary clip on the clipboard.

<br />

**See also:**

- [setPrimaryClip(ClipData)](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/ClipboardManager#setPrimaryClip(android.content.ClipData))  

### getPrimaryClip

Added in[API level 11](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/manifest/uses-sdk-element#ApiLevels)  

```
public ClipData getPrimaryClip ()
```

Returns the current primary clip on the clipboard.*If the application is not the default IME or does not have input focus this return`null`.*

<br />

|                                       Returns                                        ||
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------|
| [ClipData](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/ClipData) | <br /> |

