### getPrimaryClipDescription

Added in[API level 11](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/manifest/uses-sdk-element#ApiLevels)  

```
public ClipDescription getPrimaryClipDescription ()
```

Returns a description of the current primary clip on the clipboard but not a copy of its data.

*If the application is not the default IME or does not have input focus this return`null`.*

<br />

|                                              Returns                                               ||
|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------|
| [ClipDescription](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/ClipDescription) | <br /> |

**See also:**

- [setPrimaryClip(ClipData)](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/ClipboardManager#setPrimaryClip(android.content.ClipData))  

### getText

Added in[API level 11](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/manifest/uses-sdk-element#ApiLevels)  

```
public CharSequence getText ()
```

<br />

**This method is deprecated.**   
Use[getPrimaryClip()](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/ClipboardManager#getPrimaryClip())instead. This retrieves the primary clip and tries to coerce it to a string.

Returns the text on the clipboard. It will eventually be possible to store types other than text too, in which case this will return null if the type cannot be coerced to text.

<br />

|                                        Returns                                         ||
|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------|
| [CharSequence](https://developer.android.com/reference/java/lang/CharSequence) | <br /> |

### hasPrimaryClip

Added in[API level 11](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/manifest/uses-sdk-element#ApiLevels)  

```
public boolean hasPrimaryClip ()
```

Returns true if there is currently a primary clip on the clipboard.*If the application is not the default IME or the does not have input focus this will return`false`.*

<br />

|      Returns      ||
|-----------|--------|
| `boolean` | <br /> |

### hasText

Added in[API level 11](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/manifest/uses-sdk-element#ApiLevels)  

```
public boolean hasText ()
```

<br />

**This method is deprecated.**   
Use[hasPrimaryClip()](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/ClipboardManager#hasPrimaryClip())instead.

Returns true if the clipboard contains text; false otherwise.

<br />

