### setPrimaryClip

Added in[API level 11](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/manifest/uses-sdk-element#ApiLevels)  

```
public void setPrimaryClip (ClipData clip)
```

Sets the current primary clip on the clipboard. This is the clip that is involved in normal cut and paste operations.

<br />

|                                      Parameters                                      ||
|--------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `clip` | `ClipData`: The clipped data item to set. This value cannot be`null`. <br /> |

**See also:**

- [getPrimaryClip()](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/ClipboardManager#getPrimaryClip())
- [clearPrimaryClip()](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/ClipboardManager#clearPrimaryClip())  

### setText

Added in[API level 11](https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/manifest/uses-sdk-element#ApiLevels)  

```
public void setText (CharSequence text)
```

<br />

**This method is deprecated.**   
Use[setPrimaryClip(android.content.ClipData)](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/ClipboardManager#setPrimaryClip(android.content.ClipData))instead. This creates a ClippedItem holding the given text and sets it as the primary clip. It has no label or icon.

Sets the contents of the clipboard to the specified text.

<br />

|          Parameters           ||
|--------|-----------------------|
| `text` | `CharSequence` <br /> |